  "summaries": [
    {
      "id": 878940,
      "category": "team",
      "content": "@kyotozzx reported a JWT algorithm confusion vulnerability in the `v1` API of `connect.8x8.com`. The JWT verifier did not enforce algorithm pinning and would accept HS256 tokens signed with the RSA public key used as an HMAC secret. \n\nExploitation required knowledge of a target user's non-enumerable UUID and an active server-side session for that user. Under these conditions, forged tokens were accepted by `v1` read endpoints for account information retrieval. All state-changing endpoints independently rejected forged tokens, limiting impact to read-only access without privilege persistence or account takeover.\n\n**Remediation:**\n\nThe `v1` API verifier now enforces RS256 algorithm pinning, rejecting any tokens using alternative signature algorithms. The fix has been deployed to production and verified effective.\n\nWe thank @kyotozzx for the thorough analysis and detailed proof of concept.\n",
      "updated_at": "2026-07-22T04:14:32.584Z",
